<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7057] Store Server Load in a Table</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7057</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the server hart beat sends over server load and region loads.  This is used to display and store metrics about a region server.  It is also used to remember the sequence id of flushes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be moved into an HBase table.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Allow the last sequence id to persist over a master restart.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;That would allow the balancer to have a more complete picture of what&apos;s happened in the past.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Allow tools to be created to monitor hbase using hbase.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Simplify/remove the heartbeat.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
